    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-01-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-01-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="494" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                <head>No. 490.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Señor <persName type="to">Navarro</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-01-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 3,
                                1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your two notes of the 28th of
                            August and 18th of October last, concerning the complaint of your
                            government in regard to <pb facs="0948" n="824" xml:id="pg_824"/> the
                            acts of a band headed by one Robert E. Martin, I have the honor and
                            pleasure of informing you that the Secretary of the Interior, under date
                            of the 28th ultimo, advises this Department that the governor of the
                            Territory of Arizona has been instructed to investigate the complaint so
                            far as to the hiding place of Martin being within that Territory, and
                            that should he be found within that jurisdiction the authorities there
                            are to take such measures as may be within their power to breakup any
                            band of robbers led by him and to preserve peace upon the frontier
                            between the two countries.</p>
                <p>Accept, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
